data.title: The New York Times
data.meta_description: Correction on Sept 13 article about reality television show in Britain on which contestants are competing for role in Andrew Lloyd Webber's new production of The Sound of Music
data.text: An article in The Arts on Wednesday about a reality television show in Britain on which contestants are competing for the role of Maria in Andrew Lloyd Webber's new production of "The Sound of Music" misidentified the one who was "saved" by Lord Lloyd Webber in last Saturday's second "sing-off," resulting in the elimination of Aoife Mulholland. It was Siobhan Dillon, not Helena Blackman.
